Obama and Senator Claire McCaskill plan to introduce a bill to improve care for wounded soldiers at military hospitals.
The US Defense Department is reviewing care standards following reports of neglect at Walter Reed.
President George W. Bush's commitment to veterans is emphasized.
Investigations are ongoing, with a focus on bureaucratic issues causing delays in treatment.
Defense Secretary Robert Gates vows accountability and swift action to address the unacceptable conditions.
The situation has sparked outrage and calls for reform to ensure proper care for wounded soldiers and prevent bureaucratic obstacles in the future.
